  "chunk_index": 21,
  "summary": "Jimmy Sycamore lures Bondel away from the Countess to the library, where Bill Everly is waiting. Bill expresses anxiety regarding Bondel's involvement in the \"seven-faced clock club\" matter, fearing someone might be hurt, as happened to Ronnie. Despite these concerns, Bondel remains determined to stay involved.\n\nThe group discusses a mysterious formula held by either Herr Eberhard or Sir Oswald. Bill suggests the formula will be handed to the Air Minister tonight, which will eventually allow it to fall into the hands of O'Roke. Jimmy notes that if Sir Stanley Digby intends to take the formula upon his return to town tomorrow, something significant must occur tonight. Jimmy also mentions seeing a man in the hall, wondering if it was Watson or Lestrade, though Bill believes it was Watson.\n\nTo monitor the situation, Jimmy and Bill decide to take turns on watch. They toss a coin to decide; it lands on tails, meaning Jimmy takes the first watch and will wake Bill at three o'clock. Bondel expresses suspicion toward the Countess, but Bill defends her, citing a guarantee from the Hungarian embassy. After Bondel retires to bed, Jimmy reveals he possesses a powerful blued-steel automatic pistol obtained through his servant, Stevens. After Bill repeatedly says goodnight and departs, Jimmy is left alone to begin his watch.",
